&lt;p&gt;Having &amp;lt;scope&amp;gt;provided&amp;lt;/scope&amp;gt; is fairly common, as you know.  Many Java webapps, for example, include the servlet-api, jsp-api, and related jars with provided scope on their classpath.  So here&apos;s my vote for fixing it soon &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
